Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveSadiq Ango Abdullahi, the son of the convener of Northern Elders Forum (NEF), Ango Abdullahi, kidnapped on the Kaduna-Abuja train has won the PDP primary for the Sabon Gari federal constituency.
Sadiq was allegedly released May 2 after spending days with the terrorists who abducted him and 60 others March 28.
But Ango Abdullahi, a former Vice Chancellor of Ahmadu Bello University, told the Daily Trust he still prays and hopes that his son will be released soon.
While in captivity, Â Sadiq won with 28 votes as he defeated his rivals, including Hadiza Muhammad, Salisu Abdulhamid and Miss Paulina.
